name: False or misleading information
text: §431:14-115  False or misleading information.  No person or organization shall wilfully withhold information from or knowingly give false or misleading information to the commissioner, any statistical agency designated by the commissioner, any rating organization, or any insurer, which will affect the rates or premiums chargeable under this article.  Violation of this section shall subject the one guilty of such violation to the penalties provided in section 431:14-117. [L 1987, c 347, pt of §2]
